{"basic_builder": {"appname": "TA-hitachi-vsp-one-block-add-on-for-splunk", "friendly_name": "Hitachi VSP One Block Add-on for Splunk", "version": "1.0.0", "author": "Karthik Raja Balasubramanian and Raghavi Manga", "description": "The Hitachi VSP One Block Add-on for Splunk connects to the VSP 360 analytics database and brings storage data into Splunk. It collects three types of data: configuration details, performance metrics, and synthetic metrics for Hitachi storage resources such as arrays, pools, volumes, ports, and drives.\n\nThe add-on uses the VSP 360 REST API to query resource data, transforms the API response into Splunk events, and indexes the data with separate source types for configuration, performance, and synthetic metrics. It also enriches events with key identifiers such as storage serial number, instance ID, storage name, and model to make searching and dashboarding easier.\n\nThe add-on is designed to give Splunk users a simple and scalable way to monitor Hitachi storage environments from VSP 360, supporting dashboards, analytics, troubleshooting, correlation, and alerting.", "theme": "#65A637", "large_icon": "", "small_icon": "", "visible": true, "tab_version": "4.5.1", "tab_build_no": "0", "build_no": 1}, "data_input_builder": {"datainputs": [{"index": "default", "sourcetype": "hitachi:vspblock:config", "interval": "60", "use_external_validation": true, "streaming_mode_xml": true, "name": "vspblock_config", "title": "vspblock_config", "description": "", "type": "customized", "parameters": [{"required": true, "name": "collect_all_resource_types", "label": "collect_all_resource_types", "default_value": "true", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "true"}, {"required": false, "name": "resource_types_csv", "label": "resource_types_csv", "default_value": "", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": ""}, {"required": false, "name": "max_attributes_per_request", "label": "max_attributes_per_request", "default_value": "25", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "25"}, {"required": false, "name": "lookback_minutes", "label": "lookback_minutes", "default_value": "60", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "60"}], "data_inputs_options": [{"type": "customized_var", "name": "collect_all_resource_types", "title": "collect_all_resource_types", "description": "", "required_on_edit": false, "required_on_create": true, "format_type": "text", "default_value": "true", "placeholder": ""}, {"type": "customized_var", "name": "resource_types_csv", "title": "resource_types_csv", "description": "", "required_on_edit": false, "required_on_create": false, "format_type": "text", "default_value": "", "placeholder": ""}, {"type": "customized_var", "name": "max_attributes_per_request", "title": "max_attributes_per_request", "description": "", "required_on_edit": false, "required_on_create": false, "format_type": "text", "default_value": "25", "placeholder": ""}, {"type": "customized_var", "name": "lookback_minutes", "title": "lookback_minutes", "description": "", "required_on_edit": false, "required_on_create": false, "format_type": "text", "default_value": "60", "placeholder": ""}], "code": "# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n\"\"\"\nVSP 360 Configuration Modular Input (Splunk Add-on Builder).\n\n- Collects configuration (scalar) metrics from VSP 360 via dbapi.do?action=query\n- Emits ONE event per (signature, attribute_name)\n- Uses VSP 360 query window endTime as Splunk _time (snapshot-as-of semantics)\n- Null-fills missing schema attributes for consistent Splunk field coverage\n- Caches array identity (storage_name, storage_model) from raidStorage and injects into all events\n- Checkpointed window per resource_type per stanza\n- 60s micro-guard against rapid duplicate scheduler triggers\n\nSourcetype: hitachi:vspblock:config\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport time\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom vsp360_common import (\n    b,\n    VSP360Client,\n    stanza_name,\n    chunk_list,\n    mql_for,\n    parse_signature,\n    format_csad_time,\n    parse_csad_time,\n    unwrap_scalar,\n    vsp360_host_label,\n    normalize_utc_offset,\n)\nfrom vsp360_schema import CONFIG_ATTRS as ATTRS\n\n_DUPLICATE_GUARD_SEC = 60\n\n\ndef validate_input(helper, definition):\n    params = definition.parameters\n    collect_all = b(params.get(\"collect_all_resource_types\"), True)\n    resource_types = (params.get(\"resource_types_csv\") or \"\").strip()\n    if not collect_all and not resource_types:\n        raise ValueError(\"Either set collect_all_resource_types=true or provide resource_types_csv.\")\n\n    v = (params.get(\"max_attributes_per_request\") or \"\").strip()\n    if v:\n        int(v)\n\n    lb = (params.get(\"lookback_minutes\") or \"\").strip()\n    if lb:\n        int(lb)\n\n    return True\n\n\ndef collect_events(helper, ew):\n    base_url_raw = (helper.get_global_setting(\"vsp360_base_url\") or \"\").strip()\n    vsp360_host = vsp360_host_label(base_url_raw)\n    client_id = (helper.get_global_setting(\"client_id\") or \"\").strip()\n    client_secret = (helper.get_global_setting(\"client_secret\") or \"\").strip()\n    realm = (helper.get_global_setting(\"realm\") or \"vsp360\").strip()\n    dataset = (helper.get_global_setting(\"dataset\") or \"defaultDs\").strip()\n\n    timeout = int(helper.get_global_setting(\"timeout_seconds\") or 90)\n    process_sync = b(helper.get_global_setting(\"process_sync\"), True)\n\n    utc_offset_raw = (helper.get_global_setting(\"utc_offset\") or \"\").strip() or None\n    utc_offset = None\n    if utc_offset_raw:\n        utc_offset = normalize_utc_offset(utc_offset_raw)\n        if utc_offset != utc_offset_raw.strip():\n            helper.log_warning(f\"utc_offset reformatted: '{utc_offset_raw}' -> '{utc_offset}'.\")\n\n    if not base_url_raw or not client_id or not client_secret:\n        helper.log_error(\"Missing required global settings: vsp360_base_url, client_id, client_secret.\")\n        return\n\n    collect_all = b(helper.get_arg(\"collect_all_resource_types\"), True)\n    resource_types_csv = (helper.get_arg(\"resource_types_csv\") or \"\").strip()\n    max_attrs = int(helper.get_arg(\"max_attributes_per_request\") or 25)\n    lookback_minutes = int(helper.get_arg(\"lookback_minutes\") or 60)\n    if lookback_minutes <= 0:\n        lookback_minutes = 60\n\n    stanza = stanza_name(helper)\n\n    if collect_all:\n        resource_types = sorted(list(ATTRS.keys()))\n    else:\n        resource_types = [x.strip() for x in resource_types_csv.split(\",\") if x.strip()]\n\n    if \"raidStorage\" in resource_types:\n        resource_types = [\"raidStorage\"] + [rt for rt in resource_types if rt != \"raidStorage\"]\n\n    client = VSP360Client(base_url_raw, realm, dataset, client_id, client_secret, timeout)\n    try:\n        now_epoch = int(time.time())\n        end_time = format_csad_time(now_epoch, utc_offset)\n        end_epoch = parse_csad_time(end_time, utc_offset)\n\n        COMMON_LABELS: Dict[str, Dict[str, Any]] = {}\n        total_events = 0\n\n        for rt in resource_types:\n            if rt not in ATTRS:\n                helper.log_warning(f\"Unknown resource_type '{rt}' (not in embedded schema); skipping.\")\n                continue\n\n            cp_key = f\"configuration::{stanza}::{rt}\"\n            cp = helper.get_check_point(cp_key) or {}\n\n            last_run_epoch = int(cp.get(\"last_run_epoch\", 0) or 0)\n            if last_run_epoch and (now_epoch - last_run_epoch) < _DUPLICATE_GUARD_SEC:\n                helper.log_info(\n                    f\"Skipping {rt}: last run {now_epoch - last_run_epoch}s ago \"\n                    f\"(<{_DUPLICATE_GUARD_SEC}s duplicate guard).\"\n                )\n                continue\n\n            start_time = cp.get(\"last_end_time\")\n            if not start_time:\n                start_epoch = now_epoch - (lookback_minutes * 60)\n                start_time = format_csad_time(start_epoch, utc_offset)\n\n            attrs = sorted(list(set(ATTRS.get(rt) or [])))\n            chunks = chunk_list(attrs, max_attrs)\n\n            merged: Dict[str, Dict[str, Any]] = {}\n            helper.log_info(\n                f\"Collecting config {rt}: attrs={len(attrs)} chunks={len(chunks)} \"\n                f\"window={start_time}->{end_time}\"\n            )\n\n            for ch in chunks:\n                try:\n                    mql = mql_for(\"configuration\", rt, ch)\n                    resp = client.query(\n                        mql,\n                        start_time,\n                        end_time,\n                        process_sync=process_sync,\n                        utc_offset=utc_offset,\n                    )\n\n                    results = resp.get(\"result\") or []\n                    if not results:\n                        helper.log_warning(f\"No results returned for configuration {rt} chunk (attrs={len(ch)})\")\n\n                    for item in results:\n                        sig = item.get(\"signature\")\n                        if not sig:\n                            continue\n                        merged.setdefault(sig, {\"signature\": sig})\n                        for attr, val in item.items():\n                            if attr == \"signature\":\n                                continue\n                            merged[sig][attr] = val\n                except Exception as e:\n                    helper.log_error(f\"Chunk failed for configuration {rt} (attrs={len(ch)}): {e}\")\n                    continue\n\n            expected_attrs = set(ATTRS.get(rt) or [])\n            emitted = 0\n\n            for raw_sig, obj in merged.items():\n                serial, inst = parse_signature(raw_sig)\n\n                emit_sig = raw_sig.replace(\"^\", \":\") if isinstance(raw_sig, str) else raw_sig\n                emit_inst = inst.replace(\"^\", \":\") if isinstance(inst, str) else inst\n\n                if rt == \"raidStorage\" and serial:\n                    n_val, _, _ = unwrap_scalar(obj.get(\"name\"), numeric_coerce=False)\n                    m_val, _, _ = unwrap_scalar(obj.get(\"modelName\"), numeric_coerce=False)\n                    COMMON_LABELS[serial] = {\n                        \"storage_name\": n_val,\n                        \"storage_model\": m_val,\n                    }\n\n                labels = COMMON_LABELS.get(serial) or {}\n\n                for attr in sorted(expected_attrs):\n                    raw_val = obj.get(attr)\n                    data, attr_name, unit = unwrap_scalar(raw_val, numeric_coerce=False) if raw_val is not None else (None, None, None)\n\n                    out = {\n                        \"category\": \"configuration\",\n                        \"resource_type\": rt,\n                        \"attribute_name\": attr,\n                        \"value\": data,\n                        \"unit\": unit,\n                        \"signature\": emit_sig,\n                        \"storage_serial\": serial,\n                        \"instance_id\": emit_inst,\n                        \"collection_time\": end_time,\n                        \"vsp360_host\": vsp360_host,\n                        \"storage_name\": labels.get(\"storage_name\"),\n                        \"storage_model\": labels.get(\"storage_model\"),\n                    }\n\n                    event = helper.new_event(\n                        source=vsp360_host,\n                        index=helper.get_output_index(),\n                        sourcetype=\"hitachi:vspblock:config\",\n                        time=end_epoch,\n                        data=json.dumps(out),\n                    )\n                    ew.write_event(event)\n                    emitted += 1\n\n            total_events += emitted\n            helper.log_info(f\"Emitted {emitted} config events for {rt}\")\n\n            if emitted > 0:\n                helper.save_check_point(cp_key, {\"last_end_time\": end_time, \"last_run_epoch\": now_epoch})\n                helper.log_info(\n                    f\"Config checkpoint saved {cp_key} last_end_time={end_time} last_run_epoch={now_epoch}\"\n                )\n            else:\n                helper.log_warning(\n                    f\"Not checkpointing {rt} because 0 events were emitted (will retry next run).\"\n                )\n\n        helper.log_info(f\"Total config events emitted this run: {total_events}\")\n\n    finally:\n        client.close()", "customized_options": [{"name": "collect_all_resource_types", "value": "true"}, {"name": "resource_types_csv", "value": ""}, {"name": "max_attributes_per_request", "value": "25"}, {"name": "lookback_minutes", "value": "60"}], "uuid": "1122100f48d64f868c1102fd8867e395"}, {"index": "default", "sourcetype": "hitachi:vspblock:perf", "interval": "60", "use_external_validation": true, "streaming_mode_xml": true, "name": "vspblock_perf", "title": "vspblock_perf", "description": "", "type": "customized", "parameters": [{"required": true, "name": "collect_all_resource_types", "label": "collect_all_resource_types", "default_value": "true", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "true"}, {"required": false, "name": "resource_types_csv", "label": "resource_types_csv", "default_value": "", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": ""}, {"required": false, "name": "max_attributes_per_request", "label": "max_attributes_per_request", "default_value": "25", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "25"}, {"required": false, "name": "lookback_minutes", "label": "lookback_minutes", "default_value": "60", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "60"}], "data_inputs_options": [{"type": "customized_var", "name": "collect_all_resource_types", "title": "collect_all_resource_types", "description": "", "required_on_edit": false, "required_on_create": true, "format_type": "text", "default_value": "true", "placeholder": ""}, {"type": "customized_var", "name": "resource_types_csv", "title": "resource_types_csv", "description": "", "required_on_edit": false, "required_on_create": false, "format_type": "text", "default_value": "", "placeholder": ""}, {"type": "customized_var", "name": "max_attributes_per_request", "title": "max_attributes_per_request", "description": "", "required_on_edit": false, "required_on_create": false, "format_type": "text", "default_value": "25", "placeholder": ""}, {"type": "customized_var", "name": "lookback_minutes", "title": "lookback_minutes", "description": "", "required_on_edit": false, "required_on_create": false, "format_type": "text", "default_value": "60", "placeholder": ""}], "code": "# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n\"\"\"\nVSP 360 Performance Modular Input (Splunk Add-on Builder).\n\n- Collects performance (timeseries) metrics from VSP 360 via dbapi.do?action=query\n- Emits ONE event per (signature, metric_name, sample_time)\n- Sets Splunk _time to the precise sample epoch (derived from timeseries start + interval)\n- Chunking: splits >max_attributes_per_request into multiple MQL queries and merges by signature\n- Identity enrichment: fetches raidStorage name/model (scalar) once per run and injects\n- Checkpointing: stores the last collected endTime per resource_type per stanza\n\nSourcetype: hitachi:vspblock:perf\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport time\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom vsp360_common import (\n    b,\n    VSP360Client,\n    stanza_name,\n    chunk_list,\n    mql_for,\n    parse_signature,\n    format_csad_time,\n    unwrap_scalar,\n    vsp360_host_label,\n    normalize_utc_offset,\n    expand_timeseries,\n)\nfrom vsp360_schema import PERF_ATTRS as ATTRS\n\n_DUPLICATE_GUARD_SEC = 60\n\n\ndef validate_input(helper, definition):\n    params = definition.parameters\n    collect_all = b(params.get(\"collect_all_resource_types\"), True)\n    resource_types = (params.get(\"resource_types_csv\") or \"\").strip()\n    if not collect_all and not resource_types:\n        raise ValueError(\"Either set collect_all_resource_types=true or provide resource_types_csv.\")\n\n    v = (params.get(\"max_attributes_per_request\") or \"\").strip()\n    if v:\n        int(v)\n\n    lb = (params.get(\"lookback_minutes\") or \"\").strip()\n    if lb:\n        int(lb)\n\n    return True\n\n\ndef _load_storage_identity(helper, client: VSP360Client, start_time: str, end_time: str,\n                          process_sync: bool, utc_offset: Optional[str]) -> Dict[str, Dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Fetch raidStorage name/model once per run to enrich perf events.\"\"\"\n    labels: Dict[str, Dict[str, Any]] = {}\n    try:\n        mql = mql_for(\"configuration\", \"raidStorage\", [\"name\", \"modelName\"])\n        resp = client.query(mql, start_time, end_time, process_sync=process_sync, utc_offset=utc_offset)\n        for item in (resp.get(\"result\") or []):\n            sig = item.get(\"signature\")\n            if not sig:\n                continue\n            serial, _inst = parse_signature(sig)\n            if not serial:\n                continue\n            n_val, _, _ = unwrap_scalar(item.get(\"name\"), numeric_coerce=False)\n            m_val, _, _ = unwrap_scalar(item.get(\"modelName\"), numeric_coerce=False)\n            labels[serial] = {\"storage_name\": n_val, \"storage_model\": m_val}\n        helper.log_info(f\"Loaded raidStorage identity for {len(labels)} arrays (for perf enrichment)\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        helper.log_warning(f\"Perf identity enrichment skipped (raidStorage lookup failed): {e}\")\n    return labels\n\n\ndef collect_events(helper, ew):\n    base_url_raw = (helper.get_global_setting(\"vsp360_base_url\") or \"\").strip()\n    vsp360_host = vsp360_host_label(base_url_raw)\n    client_id = (helper.get_global_setting(\"client_id\") or \"\").strip()\n    client_secret = (helper.get_global_setting(\"client_secret\") or \"\").strip()\n    realm = (helper.get_global_setting(\"realm\") or \"vsp360\").strip()\n    dataset = (helper.get_global_setting(\"dataset\") or \"defaultDs\").strip()\n\n    timeout = int(helper.get_global_setting(\"timeout_seconds\") or 90)\n    process_sync = b(helper.get_global_setting(\"process_sync\"), True)\n\n    utc_offset_raw = (helper.get_global_setting(\"utc_offset\") or \"\").strip() or None\n    utc_offset = None\n    if utc_offset_raw:\n        utc_offset = normalize_utc_offset(utc_offset_raw)\n        if utc_offset != utc_offset_raw.strip():\n            helper.log_warning(f\"utc_offset reformatted: '{utc_offset_raw}' -> '{utc_offset}'.\")\n\n    if not base_url_raw or not client_id or not client_secret:\n        helper.log_error(\"Missing required global settings: vsp360_base_url, client_id, client_secret.\")\n        return\n\n    collect_all = b(helper.get_arg(\"collect_all_resource_types\"), True)\n    resource_types_csv = (helper.get_arg(\"resource_types_csv\") or \"\").strip()\n    max_attrs = int(helper.get_arg(\"max_attributes_per_request\") or 25)\n    lookback_minutes = int(helper.get_arg(\"lookback_minutes\") or 60)\n    if lookback_minutes <= 0:\n        lookback_minutes = 60\n\n    stanza = stanza_name(helper)\n\n    if collect_all:\n        resource_types = sorted(list(ATTRS.keys()))\n    else:\n        resource_types = [x.strip() for x in resource_types_csv.split(\",\") if x.strip()]\n\n    client = VSP360Client(base_url_raw, realm, dataset, client_id, client_secret, timeout)\n    try:\n        now_epoch = int(time.time())\n        end_time = format_csad_time(now_epoch, utc_offset)\n\n        enrich_start_epoch = now_epoch - (24 * 60 * 60)\n        enrich_start_time = format_csad_time(enrich_start_epoch, utc_offset)\n        COMMON_LABELS = _load_storage_identity(helper, client, enrich_start_time, end_time, process_sync, utc_offset)\n\n        total_events = 0\n\n        for rt in resource_types:\n            if rt not in ATTRS:\n                helper.log_warning(f\"Unknown resource_type '{rt}' (not in embedded PERF_ATTRS); skipping.\")\n                continue\n\n            cp_key = f\"performance::{stanza}::{rt}\"\n            cp = helper.get_check_point(cp_key) or {}\n\n            last_run_epoch = int(cp.get(\"last_run_epoch\", 0) or 0)\n            if last_run_epoch and (now_epoch - last_run_epoch) < _DUPLICATE_GUARD_SEC:\n                helper.log_info(\n                    f\"Skipping {rt}: last run {now_epoch - last_run_epoch}s ago \"\n                    f\"(<{_DUPLICATE_GUARD_SEC}s duplicate guard).\"\n                )\n                continue\n\n            start_time = cp.get(\"last_end_time\")\n            if not start_time:\n                start_epoch = now_epoch - (lookback_minutes * 60)\n                start_time = format_csad_time(start_epoch, utc_offset)\n\n            attrs = sorted(list(set(ATTRS.get(rt) or [])))\n            chunks = chunk_list(attrs, max_attrs)\n\n            merged: Dict[str, Dict[str, Any]] = {}\n            helper.log_info(f\"Collecting perf {rt}: attrs={len(attrs)} chunks={len(chunks)} window={start_time}->{end_time}\")\n\n            for ch in chunks:\n                try:\n                    mql = mql_for(\"performance\", rt, ch)\n                    resp = client.query(\n                        mql,\n                        start_time,\n                        end_time,\n                        process_sync=process_sync,\n                        utc_offset=utc_offset,\n                    )\n                    results = resp.get(\"result\") or []\n                    if not results:\n                        helper.log_warning(f\"No results returned for performance {rt} chunk (attrs={len(ch)})\")\n\n                    for item in results:\n                        sig = item.get(\"signature\")\n                        if not sig:\n                            continue\n                        merged.setdefault(sig, {\"signature\": sig})\n                        for attr, val in item.items():\n                            if attr == \"signature\":\n                                continue\n                            merged[sig][attr] = val\n                except Exception as e:\n                    helper.log_error(f\"Chunk failed for performance {rt} (attrs={len(ch)}): {e}\")\n                    continue\n\n            emitted = 0\n\n            for raw_sig, obj in merged.items():\n                serial, inst = parse_signature(raw_sig)\n\n                emit_sig = raw_sig.replace(\"^\", \":\") if isinstance(raw_sig, str) else raw_sig\n                emit_inst = inst.replace(\"^\", \":\") if isinstance(inst, str) else inst\n\n                labels = COMMON_LABELS.get(serial) or {}\n\n                for metric_name, metric_obj in obj.items():\n                    if metric_name == \"signature\":\n                        continue\n\n                    for sample_epoch, value, interval, unit in expand_timeseries(metric_obj, utc_offset):\n                        out = {\n                            \"category\": \"performance\",\n                            \"resource_type\": rt,\n                            \"metric_name\": metric_name,\n                            \"value\": value,\n                            \"unit\": unit,\n                            \"interval\": interval,\n                            \"signature\": emit_sig,\n                            \"storage_serial\": serial,\n                            \"instance_id\": emit_inst,\n                            \"vsp360_host\": vsp360_host,\n                            \"storage_name\": labels.get(\"storage_name\"),\n                            \"storage_model\": labels.get(\"storage_model\"),\n                        }\n\n                        event = helper.new_event(\n                            source=vsp360_host,\n                            index=helper.get_output_index(),\n                            sourcetype=\"hitachi:vspblock:perf\",\n                            time=int(sample_epoch),\n                            data=json.dumps(out),\n                        )\n                        ew.write_event(event)\n                        emitted += 1\n                        total_events += 1\n\n            helper.log_info(f\"Emitted {emitted} perf events for {rt}\")\n\n            if emitted > 0:\n                helper.save_check_point(cp_key, {\"last_end_time\": end_time, \"last_run_epoch\": now_epoch})\n                helper.log_info(f\"Perf checkpoint saved {cp_key} last_end_time={end_time} last_run_epoch={now_epoch}\")\n            else:\n                helper.log_warning(f\"Not checkpointing {rt} because 0 perf events were emitted (will retry next run).\")\n\n        helper.log_info(f\"Total perf events emitted this run: {total_events}\")\n\n    finally:\n        client.close()", "customized_options": [{"name": "collect_all_resource_types", "value": "true"}, {"name": "resource_types_csv", "value": ""}, {"name": "max_attributes_per_request", "value": "25"}, {"name": "lookback_minutes", "value": "60"}], "uuid": "56eb34e2dffc43ea925d9c695e50edd7"}, {"index": "default", "sourcetype": "hitachi:vspblock:synth", "interval": "60", "use_external_validation": true, "streaming_mode_xml": true, "name": "vspblock_synth", "title": "vspblock_synth", "description": "", "type": "customized", "parameters": [{"required": true, "name": "collect_all_resource_types", "label": "collect_all_resource_types", "default_value": "true", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "true"}, {"required": false, "name": "resource_types_csv", "label": "resource_types_csv", "default_value": "", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": ""}, {"required": false, "name": "max_attributes_per_request", "label": "max_attributes_per_request", "default_value": "25", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "25"}, {"required": false, "name": "lookback_minutes", "label": "lookback_minutes", "default_value": "60", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "60"}], "data_inputs_options": [{"type": "customized_var", "name": "collect_all_resource_types", "title": "collect_all_resource_types", "description": "", "required_on_edit": false, "required_on_create": true, "format_type": "text", "default_value": "true", "placeholder": ""}, {"type": "customized_var", "name": "resource_types_csv", "title": "resource_types_csv", "description": "", "required_on_edit": false, "required_on_create": false, "format_type": "text", "default_value": "", "placeholder": ""}, {"type": "customized_var", "name": "max_attributes_per_request", "title": "max_attributes_per_request", "description": "", "required_on_edit": false, "required_on_create": false, "format_type": "text", "default_value": "25", "placeholder": ""}, {"type": "customized_var", "name": "lookback_minutes", "title": "lookback_minutes", "description": "", "required_on_edit": false, "required_on_create": false, "format_type": "text", "default_value": "60", "placeholder": ""}], "code": "# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n\"\"\"\nVSP 360 Synthetic Metrics Modular Input (Splunk Add-on Builder).\n\n- Collects synthetic (roll-up) timeseries metrics from VSP 360 via dbapi.do?action=query\n- Uses SYNTH_ATTRS from vsp360_schema.py as the single source of truth\n- Emits ONE event per (signature, metric_name, sample_time)\n- Sets Splunk _time to the precise sample epoch (derived from timeseries start + interval)\n- Chunking: splits >max_attributes_per_request into multiple MQL queries and merges by signature\n- Identity enrichment: fetches raidStorage name/model (scalar) once per run and injects\n- Checkpointing: stores the last collected endTime per resource_type per stanza\n- Safety: does NOT checkpoint when 0 events are emitted for a resource type (will retry next run)\n\nSourcetype: hitachi:vspblock:synth\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport time\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom vsp360_common import (\n    b,\n    VSP360Client,\n    stanza_name,\n    chunk_list,\n    mql_for,\n    parse_signature,\n    format_csad_time,\n    unwrap_scalar,\n    vsp360_host_label,\n    normalize_utc_offset,\n    expand_timeseries,\n)\nfrom vsp360_schema import SYNTH_ATTRS as ATTRS\n\n_DUPLICATE_GUARD_SEC = 60\n\n\ndef validate_input(helper, definition):\n    params = definition.parameters\n    collect_all = b(params.get(\"collect_all_resource_types\"), True)\n    resource_types = (params.get(\"resource_types_csv\") or \"\").strip()\n    if not collect_all and not resource_types:\n        raise ValueError(\"Either set collect_all_resource_types=true or provide resource_types_csv.\")\n\n    v = (params.get(\"max_attributes_per_request\") or \"\").strip()\n    if v:\n        int(v)\n\n    lb = (params.get(\"lookback_minutes\") or \"\").strip()\n    if lb:\n        int(lb)\n\n    return True\n\n\ndef _load_storage_identity(helper, client: VSP360Client, start_time: str, end_time: str,\n                          process_sync: bool, utc_offset: Optional[str]) -> Dict[str, Dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Fetch raidStorage name/model once per run to enrich synth events.\"\"\"\n    labels: Dict[str, Dict[str, Any]] = {}\n    try:\n        mql = mql_for(\"configuration\", \"raidStorage\", [\"name\", \"modelName\"])\n        resp = client.query(mql, start_time, end_time, process_sync=process_sync, utc_offset=utc_offset)\n        for item in (resp.get(\"result\") or []):\n            sig = item.get(\"signature\")\n            if not sig:\n                continue\n            serial, _inst = parse_signature(sig)\n            if not serial:\n                continue\n            n_val, _, _ = unwrap_scalar(item.get(\"name\"), numeric_coerce=False)\n            m_val, _, _ = unwrap_scalar(item.get(\"modelName\"), numeric_coerce=False)\n            labels[serial] = {\"storage_name\": n_val, \"storage_model\": m_val}\n        helper.log_info(f\"Loaded raidStorage identity for {len(labels)} arrays (for synth enrichment)\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        helper.log_warning(f\"Synth identity enrichment skipped (raidStorage lookup failed): {e}\")\n    return labels\n\n\ndef collect_events(helper, ew):\n    base_url_raw = (helper.get_global_setting(\"vsp360_base_url\") or \"\").strip()\n    vsp360_host = vsp360_host_label(base_url_raw)\n    client_id = (helper.get_global_setting(\"client_id\") or \"\").strip()\n    client_secret = (helper.get_global_setting(\"client_secret\") or \"\").strip()\n    realm = (helper.get_global_setting(\"realm\") or \"vsp360\").strip()\n    dataset = (helper.get_global_setting(\"dataset\") or \"defaultDs\").strip()\n\n    timeout = int(helper.get_global_setting(\"timeout_seconds\") or 90)\n    process_sync = b(helper.get_global_setting(\"process_sync\"), True)\n\n    utc_offset_raw = (helper.get_global_setting(\"utc_offset\") or \"\").strip() or None\n    utc_offset = None\n    if utc_offset_raw:\n        utc_offset = normalize_utc_offset(utc_offset_raw)\n        if utc_offset != utc_offset_raw.strip():\n            helper.log_warning(f\"utc_offset reformatted: '{utc_offset_raw}' -> '{utc_offset}'.\")\n\n    if not base_url_raw or not client_id or not client_secret:\n        helper.log_error(\"Missing required global settings: vsp360_base_url, client_id, client_secret.\")\n        return\n\n    collect_all = b(helper.get_arg(\"collect_all_resource_types\"), True)\n    resource_types_csv = (helper.get_arg(\"resource_types_csv\") or \"\").strip()\n    max_attrs = int(helper.get_arg(\"max_attributes_per_request\") or 25)\n    lookback_minutes = int(helper.get_arg(\"lookback_minutes\") or 60)\n    if lookback_minutes <= 0:\n        lookback_minutes = 60\n\n    stanza = stanza_name(helper)\n\n    if collect_all:\n        resource_types = sorted(list(ATTRS.keys()))\n    else:\n        resource_types = [x.strip() for x in resource_types_csv.split(\",\") if x.strip()]\n\n    client = VSP360Client(base_url_raw, realm, dataset, client_id, client_secret, timeout)\n    try:\n        now_epoch = int(time.time())\n        end_time = format_csad_time(now_epoch, utc_offset)\n\n        enrich_start_epoch = now_epoch - (24 * 60 * 60)\n        enrich_start_time = format_csad_time(enrich_start_epoch, utc_offset)\n        COMMON_LABELS = _load_storage_identity(helper, client, enrich_start_time, end_time, process_sync, utc_offset)\n\n        total_events = 0\n\n        for rt in resource_types:\n            if rt not in ATTRS:\n                helper.log_warning(f\"Unknown resource_type '{rt}' (not in embedded SYNTH_ATTRS); skipping.\")\n                continue\n\n            cp_key = f\"synthetic::{stanza}::{rt}\"\n            cp = helper.get_check_point(cp_key) or {}\n\n            last_run_epoch = int(cp.get(\"last_run_epoch\", 0) or 0)\n            if last_run_epoch and (now_epoch - last_run_epoch) < _DUPLICATE_GUARD_SEC:\n                helper.log_info(\n                    f\"Skipping {rt}: last run {now_epoch - last_run_epoch}s ago \"\n                    f\"(<{_DUPLICATE_GUARD_SEC}s duplicate guard).\"\n                )\n                continue\n\n            start_time = cp.get(\"last_end_time\")\n            if not start_time:\n                start_epoch = now_epoch - (lookback_minutes * 60)\n                start_time = format_csad_time(start_epoch, utc_offset)\n\n            attrs = sorted(list(set(ATTRS.get(rt) or [])))\n            chunks = chunk_list(attrs, max_attrs)\n\n            merged: Dict[str, Dict[str, Any]] = {}\n            helper.log_info(f\"Collecting synth {rt}: attrs={len(attrs)} chunks={len(chunks)} window={start_time}->{end_time}\")\n\n            for ch in chunks:\n                try:\n                    mql = mql_for(\"synthetic\", rt, ch)\n                    resp = client.query(\n                        mql,\n                        start_time,\n                        end_time,\n                        process_sync=process_sync,\n                        utc_offset=utc_offset,\n                    )\n                    results = resp.get(\"result\") or []\n                    if not results:\n                        helper.log_warning(f\"No results returned for synthetic {rt} chunk (attrs={len(ch)})\")\n\n                    for item in results:\n                        sig = item.get(\"signature\")\n                        if not sig:\n                            continue\n                        merged.setdefault(sig, {\"signature\": sig})\n                        for attr, val in item.items():\n                            if attr == \"signature\":\n                                continue\n                            merged[sig][attr] = val\n                except Exception as e:\n                    helper.log_error(f\"Chunk failed for synthetic {rt} (attrs={len(ch)}): {e}\")\n                    continue\n\n            emitted = 0\n\n            for raw_sig, obj in merged.items():\n                serial, inst = parse_signature(raw_sig)\n\n                emit_sig = raw_sig.replace(\"^\", \":\") if isinstance(raw_sig, str) else raw_sig\n                emit_inst = inst.replace(\"^\", \":\") if isinstance(inst, str) else inst\n\n                labels = COMMON_LABELS.get(serial) or {}\n\n                for metric_name, metric_obj in obj.items():\n                    if metric_name == \"signature\":\n                        continue\n\n                    for sample_epoch, value, interval, unit in expand_timeseries(metric_obj, utc_offset):\n                        out = {\n                            \"category\": \"synthetic\",\n                            \"resource_type\": rt,\n                            \"metric_name\": metric_name,\n                            \"value\": value,\n                            \"unit\": unit,\n                            \"interval\": interval,\n                            \"signature\": emit_sig,\n                            \"storage_serial\": serial,\n                            \"instance_id\": emit_inst,\n                            \"vsp360_host\": vsp360_host,\n                            \"storage_name\": labels.get(\"storage_name\"),\n                            \"storage_model\": labels.get(\"storage_model\"),\n                        }\n\n                        event = helper.new_event(\n                            source=vsp360_host,\n                            index=helper.get_output_index(),\n                            sourcetype=\"hitachi:vspblock:synth\",\n                            time=int(sample_epoch),\n                            data=json.dumps(out),\n                        )\n                        ew.write_event(event)\n                        emitted += 1\n                        total_events += 1\n\n            helper.log_info(f\"Emitted {emitted} synth events for {rt}\")\n\n            if emitted > 0:\n                helper.save_check_point(cp_key, {\"last_end_time\": end_time, \"last_run_epoch\": now_epoch})\n                helper.log_info(f\"Synth checkpoint saved {cp_key} last_end_time={end_time} last_run_epoch={now_epoch}\")\n            else:\n                helper.log_warning(f\"Not checkpointing {rt} because 0 synth events were emitted (will retry next run).\")\n\n        helper.log_info(f\"Total synth events emitted this run: {total_events}\")\n\n    finally:\n        client.close()", "customized_options": [{"name": "collect_all_resource_types", "value": "true"}, {"name": "resource_types_csv", "value": ""}, {"name": "max_attributes_per_request", "value": "25"}, {"name": "lookback_minutes", "value": "60"}], "uuid": "a9343207fa4545dd9c04d5c4abfa3fb3"}]}, "field_extraction_builder": {"hitachi:vspblock:config": {"is_parsed": true, "data_format": "json"}, "hitachi:vspblock:perf": {"is_parsed": true, "data_format": "json"}, "hitachi:vspblock:synth": {"is_parsed": true, "data_format": "json"}}, "global_settings_builder": {"global_settings": {"log_settings": {"log_level": "DEBUG"}, "customized_settings": [{"required": true, "name": "vsp360_base_url", "label": "vsp360_base_url", "default_value": "", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "https://vsp360-32.hds.com"}, {"required": true, "name": "realm", "label": "realm", "default_value": "vsp360", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "vsp360"}, {"required": false, "name": "dataset", "label": "dataset", "default_value": "defaultDs", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "defaultDs"}, {"required": true, "name": "client_id", "label": "client_id", "default_value": "", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "VSP360SA02"}, {"required": true, "name": "client_secret", "label": "client_secret", "placeholder": "", "default_value": "", "help_string": "", "type": "password", "format_type": "password", "value": ""}, {"required": false, "name": "timeout_seconds", "label": "timeout_seconds", "default_value": "90", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "90"}, {"required": false, "name": "process_sync", "label": "process_sync", "default_value": "true", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "true"}, {"required": true, "name": "utc_offset", "label": "utc_offset", "default_value": "UTC+0000", "placeholder": "", "help_string": "", "type": "text", "format_type": "text", "value": "UTC+0000"}]}}, "sourcetype_builder": {"hitachi:vspblock:config": {"metadata": {"event_count": 0, "data_input_name": "vspblock_config", "extractions_count": 0, "cims_count": 0}}, "hitachi:vspblock:perf": {"metadata": {"event_count": 0, "data_input_name": "vspblock_perf", "extractions_count": 0, "cims_count": 0}}, "hitachi:vspblock:synth": {"metadata": {"event_count": 0, "data_input_name": "vspblock_synth", "extractions_count": 0, "cims_count": 0}}}, "validation": {"validators": ["best_practice_validation", "data_model_mapping_validation", "field_extract_validation", "app_cert_validation"], "status": "job_started", "validation_id": "v_1773975293_82"}}